ountry is gradually moving towards its countdown that could yœpossibly signify the end of the crisis, if citizens resist complacency. Quoting statistics from the IMS, he, however, noted that there are 102 Ebola contacts across the country, with nearly all of the ETU nearing emptiness. 'Thirteen of the 15 counties have completed more than two of their incubation periods without a single trace of any new case, which means, that most political sub-divisions of the county, except Montserrado and Margibi Counties, have gone 28 days or more without a confirmed case,' he said."</p>
